<div class="container">
    <h2 class="post-title">Exploring the Beauty of Nature</h2>
    <p class="post-meta">Posted on January 31, 2025 by John Doe</p>
    <img src="https://www.pexels.com/photo/green-trees-under-blue-sky-123123/" alt="Nature Image" class="post-image">
    <div class="post-content">
        <p>Nature has always been a source of inspiration and tranquility. The lush green forests, the serene lakes, and the majestic mountains offer a sense of peace that is hard to find elsewhere. In this post, we will explore some of the most beautiful natural landscapes around the world.</p>
        <h3>1. The Amazon Rainforest</h3>
        <p>The Amazon Rainforest, often referred to as the "lungs of the Earth," is a vast tropical rainforest in South America. It is home to a diverse range of flora and fauna, many of which are found nowhere else on the planet.</p>
        <h3>2. The Grand Canyon</h3>
        <p>Located in Arizona, USA, the Grand Canyon is a colossal canyon carved by the Colorado River. Its immense size and intricate rock formations make it one of the most awe-inspiring natural wonders.</p>
        <h3>3. The Great Barrier Reef</h3>
        <p>Off the coast of Queensland, Australia, the Great Barrier Reef is the world's largest coral reef system. It boasts an incredible array of marine life and vibrant coral formations.</p>
        <p>Exploring these natural wonders not only provides breathtaking views but also reminds us of the importance of preserving our planet's beauty for future generations.</p>
    </div>
